NoiaButtonsFx57+ v1.0

[Buttons]
- Noia button icons for toolbars (default)
- Firefox 1 button icons for toolbars
- Firefox 2 button icons for toolbars
- Firefox 3 button icons for toolbars
- Firefox 4 button icons for toolbars

- shrink button icons on hover (default)

- autosize for button icons on nav-bar (default)
[compact=24/normal=30/touch=36]
- 18x18px (tiny) size for button icons on nav-bar
- 24x24px (small) size for button icons on nav-bar
- 30x30px (normal) size for button icons on nav-bar
- 36x36px (large) size for button icons on nav-bar

[Location Bar]
- location bar icons for go button and autocomple dropmarker

[Themes for toolbars and tabs known from 'Noia4' and 'NoiaFox' themes *]
- Noia theme (light)
- tabs below navigation toolbar for Noia theme (light)
- Noia theme (dark)
- tabs below navigation toolbar for Noia theme (dark)

* Toolbar separators and alternative tab colors can be set by modifying
'noiaui_light.css' and 'noiaui_dark.css' files.
Look for code marked with 'toolbar separator' and 'tabs color v2' and
'uncomment' it.

Added Firefox's command line as an option to access the profile folder

2.0.0

Sorry, no fancy 2.0 update. Just default number incrementation like always. ;-)

Add missing_tab_favicon_restored_brand_logo.css

Newer firefox versions show the browser brand logo as the favicon for
new tabs, except for the very first one opened when the browser starts
which has no favicon.

By using missing_tab_favicon_restored_default.css the first tab would
get the "globe" favicon looking different from the new tabs opened after
it.

Add a file to set the missing icon to the browser brand logo to make all
the empty tabs look the same.

Fix Responsive Design Icon's Opacity

@Acid-Crash spotted that one, the responsive design icon needs opacity set to zero. It looked like a big black square (instead of a cellphone) but who was I to question Mozilla's choices of icons, lol, I had no idea it was supposed to look different ;-) This fixes it.
Add css file to hide "set as desktop background"

Password viewer in login forms

[tabs] fix the multiline tabbar for FF71+

Even More AppButton Icons (DevTools)

Added all the DevTools icons. Managed to get them by KEY so it should be multi-language (except "More Tools" which unfortunately is by label). ReUsed the DOM icon for Source and the Console icon is used for both consoles. Added quotes to your list-images (syntax highlighting friendly lol).

Potential fix for non UTF-8 encoded feeds (#23)

* Retrieve feed text as an arraybuffer, convert it to a UTF-8 string in order to detect if the feed has its own encoding (such as 'windows-1251'), and if there is a different encoding, decode with that encoding type.

* Specify the UTF-8 charset since Firefox seems to use this anyway.  Resolves web console "A meta tag was used to declare the character encoding as UTF-16. This was interpreted as an UTF-8 declaration instead." message.

Since Mozilla removed the last XBL binding from Firefox, it's only a matter of time until they remove XUL support, removing the option to use userchrome.xml to patch firefox, so this update tries to fix that.

It's more tedious, but it should work past the upcoming XUL deprecation.

I decided to integrate all multi-row tabs code inside MultiRowTabLiteforFx.uc.js. This way you can enable completelly functional multi-rows by just placing the file in your chrome folder, instead of having to disable both userchrome lines and that file.
